    "causal_summary": "The system-spec-kit uses \"memory\" as a catch-all label for six distinct subsystems (SQLite + embeddings index, canonical spec-doc markdown, generated metadata files, session resume surfaces, hybrid retrieval pipeline, constitutional rules), creating onboarding friction, ~270+ inconsistent references across the codebase, and a future naming clash with Anthropic's Claude Memory tool. This spec scopes a deep-research-driven rename across the public API surface (slash commands, MCP tools, SQL tables, doc strings, frontmatter keys) without changing behavior.",
